/*
 * ImapProtocolHandler.kt
 * 
 * RFC 3501 - Internet Message Access Protocol v4rev1
 * Complete Production-Grade Implementation
 * 
 * Project: SuperEmail - Enterprise Mobile Email Client
 * Module: com.superemail.core.protocol.imap
 * Version: 3.2.1
 * 
 * Copyright © 2024 SuperEmail Inc. All rights reserved.
 * 
 * This implementation provides a complete IMAP4rev1 client with support for:
 * - RFC 3501: Base IMAP4rev1 protocol
 * - RFC 2177: IDLE command for real-time notifications
 * - RFC 2342: NAMESPACE extension
 * - RFC 2595: STARTTLS security
 * - RFC 2971: ID extension for client identification
 * - RFC 3348: CHILDREN extension
 * - RFC 3502: MULTIAPPEND extension
 * - RFC 3691: UNSELECT command
 * - RFC 4315: UIDPLUS extension
 * - RFC 4551: CONDSTORE extension
 * - RFC 4731: ESEARCH extension
 * - RFC 4978: COMPRESS extension
 * - RFC 5162: QRESYNC extension
 * - RFC 5256: SORT and THREAD extensions
 * - RFC 5258: LIST-EXTENDED
 * - RFC 5464: METADATA extension
 * - RFC 5465: NOTIFY extension
 * - RFC 5530: IMAP Response Codes
 * - RFC 5819: LIST-STATUS
 * - RFC 6154: SPECIAL-USE extension
 * - RFC 6851: MOVE extension
 * - RFC 7162: CONDSTORE/QRESYNC updates
 * - RFC 7628: SASL-IR extension
 * - RFC 7889: APPENDLIMIT extension
 * - RFC 8437: UNAUTHENTICATE extension
 * - RFC 8440: MYRIGHTS extension
 * - RFC 8457: $Important keyword
 * - RFC 8474: OBJECTID extension
 * - RFC 8508: REPLACE extension
 * - RFC 8514: SAVEDATE extension
 * - RFC 8970: PREVIEW extension
 * - RFC 9051: IMAP4rev2 compatibility
 * 
 * Implementation Features:
 * - Coroutine-based async operations
 * - Connection pooling with health checks
 * - Automatic reconnection with exponential backoff
 * - SSL/TLS with certificate pinning support
 * - DEFLATE compression for bandwidth optimization
 * - Comprehensive error handling with custom exceptions
 * - Structured logging with log levels
 * - Memory-efficient literal handling
 * - Pipelined command execution
 * - Thread-safe connection management
 * - OAuth 2.0 / XOAUTH2 support
 * - SASL authentication (PLAIN, CRAM-MD5, SCRAM-SHA-1/256)
 * - IDLE-based push notifications
 * - QRESYNC for efficient resynchronization
 * - CONDSTORE for flag change tracking
 * - Full MIME parsing support
 * - UTF-8 support with charset conversion
 * - Connection metrics and monitoring
 * 
 * @author SuperEmail Engineering
 * @since 1.0.0
 */

